            <h1 class="section-title">Scottish Archives</h1>
            <p>
Are you undertaking research using Scottish archives? Have you considered submitting an article to Scottish Archives, the journal of the Scottish Records Association? Articles in this annual, peer-reviewed journal, focus on the use of and interpretation of Scottish archives and historical sources both within Scotland and further afield. The Editors will consider any submission that makes use of archival material to explore historical matters relevant to Scotland. Article length should be between 4,000 and 6,000 words, but longer submissions may be considered. Under our Green Open Access Policy, articles are published on the Association's website one year after print publication which enables your research to be disseminated to a wide audience.</p>
            <p>Please contact the Editors, Charlotte Berry and Cathryn Spence at: <a href="mailto:editorscottisharchives@gmail.com">editorscottisharchives@gmail.com</a> if you wish to propose or submit a paper.</p>
            <p>If you have already published a book, you might like to consider sending a copy for review to our Reviews Editor who can be contacted at: <a href="mailto:reviewseditorscottisharchives@gmail.com">reviewseditorscottisharchives@gmail.com</a>.</p>
            <p>The Editorial Team at Scottish Archives look forward to hearing from you!</p>
